list(address).details: Emits a {List} event. Notes: - It is not an error to list an address that is already listed. Requirements: - The caller must be the admin.

params.addr: The address to list in the archive, which should be a contract.

transferAdmin(address).details: Notes: - Does not revert if the admin is the same. - This function can potentially leave the contract without an admin, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the admin. Requirements: - `msg.sender` must be the contract admin.

params.newAdmin: The address of the new admin.

unlist(address).details: Emits an {Unlist} event. Notes: - It is not an error to unlist an address that is not already listed. Requirements: - The caller must be the admin.

params.addr: The address to unlist from the archive, which is usually a contract address.

admin().notice: The address of the admin account or contract.

isListed(address).notice: A boolean flag that indicates whether the provided address is part of the archive.

list(address).notice: Lists an address in the archive.

transferAdmin(address).notice: Transfers the contract admin to a new address.

unlist(address).notice: Unlists an address from the archive.
